A korean dipping sauce that goes great with Korean grilled meat dishes, or simply with a tray of veggies cut into sticks (eg; cucumbers, peppers, carrots)

Credit to [Maangchi](https://www.maangchi.com/recipe/ssamjang) (with modifications)

# Ingredients
* 1/4 cup doenjang (fermented soybean paste) [1][1]
* 1 tbs gochujang (hot pepper paste) [2][2]
* 1 stalk of minced green onion
* 2 cloves of minced garlic
* 1/3 cup chopped onion (preferably sweet, like purple, white, or shallots!)
* 3 ts honey or maple syrup
* 2 ts toasted sesame seeds
* 1 ts toasted sesame oil

[1]: If you can't source doenjang locally, use miso paste (the darker the better), though depending on the miso's flavor you may need to adjust the other ingredients to taste
[2]: If you can't source gochujang, here's [a recipe](https://www.maangchi.com/recipe/gochujang) - also courtesy of Maangchi!

# Instructions
* Mix it all together in a bowl and serve with veggie sticks or with a grilled Korean meat dish such as [Galbi](https://www.maangchi.com/recipe/la-galbi)!
